rComments: By far my favourite course taken at U of T. Extremely interesting and well-organized lecture material and readings. Very caring, kind and encouraging professor. Would love to take another course taught by her again.

Not a good lecturer. Very difficult to follow her lectures. She reads very quickly. Several students have asked her to speak more slowly during class, myself included, and she either forgot or doesn't care.

Awful instructor; like the previous comment says she reads off her papers very quickly, completely monotone, doesn't even look up, I don't know how she breathes. It is impossible to take notes. I am 4th year student and this is by far the worst course I took. It is evident that she does not really know her stuff, she'd be lost without her notes.

She basically reads her script in a super quick pace throughout the two hours in monotone. Can't even catch up with her speed while taking notes. If you are new to art history, I will not recommend Susan's class.
